abstract = {Player involvement in the process of game development has become a de-facto standard
in both industry and academia. Participation is intended to empower players, while
helping designers create better games. However, participation also introduces uncertainty
regarding players' and designers' relative roles, and creates new concerns over the
exploitation of players, marginalization of designers, and the quality of game design
outcomes. In this workshop, we invite the games research community to critically reflect
on methods used to facilitate player participation, with the goal of establishing
dialogue around meaningful and constructive player involvement.},
