abstract = { Procedural content generation techniques can be used during game design to aid in
exploration and expedite the content creation process. But this comes with the challenge
of exploring a large quantity of generated content. This challenge is exacerbated
by the lack of proper supporting tools. We contend that such tools should encourage
exploration, and respect the nature of design judgment. We present a visual analytics
