doi = {10.1145/2652524.2652525},
abstract = {Context: Software projects often have four objectives; to produce the required functionality,
in budget and in schedule, with acceptable quality. That statement may be true for
most of the ordinary software development projects, but are these objectives enough
for game development, where creativity and artistic aspects have a major role? Goal:
