usable and effective interactive computing systems. Topics of interest include the
design and development of systems with new interaction techniques and modalities,
multi-device interaction, service front-ends, mobile and pervasive systems, large-scale
and big data applications, as well as novel development methods and processes. EICS
focuses on methods, techniques and tools that support designing and developing interactive
systems.The Conference brings together people who study or practice the engineering
of interactive systems, drawing from a broad range of disciplines such as Human-Computer
