address = {New York, NY, USA},
url = {https://doi.org/10.1145/3176653.3176715},
doi = {10.1145/3176653.3176715},
abstract = {Through the development and evolution of digital entertainment industry, the production
of video games is more and more sophisticated, portable and has reached every corner
of the world. Along with growing number of players (2.2 billion in 2017), game is
becoming the surely deserving new media. Today the experience provided by video game
is not limited to only "Play", but also to perceive and cognize. Under this circumstance,
Game Scenes, which provides environment to characters and stories, becomes a new carrier
of culture and art. By analyzing hundreds of video games on multiple platforms, this
paper summarizes three main methods on cultural architecture design, and then the
author takes her team's game design work for example to explore the scene design of
city construction game and the development process of cultural architecture design
by using the methods.},
