Cognitive Impairment (MCI). Our solution aims (a) to automatically detect patterns
of mental behaviour based on game-play metrics of large groups of older players, (b)
to establish novel game design and development paradigms integrating a continuous
and ongoing cognitive training process for older individuals with mild cognitive impairment,
(c) to monitor the player's capacity to perform real-life training exercises through
the adoption of Virtual reality technologies and provide objective feedback and (d)
to identify a methodological user centered design framework for building VR games
for older adults.},
